uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data

Class CachedIndexedProducer<T extends Indexed>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.CachedIndexedProducer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    TypeConverter<T,java.lang.Number>, IndexedProducer<T>, Targetted<T>

    public class CachedIndexedProducer<T extends Indexed>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IndexedProducer<T>
    Decorator around a IndexProducer that caches values. The entire cache is hidden behind a SoftReference so if memory becomes tight the cache is cleared. This has less overhead than hiding individual elements behind a reference but it means we clear the entire cache if memory becomes tight.
